<H1 ALIGN=CENTER>
Yanomam Language Family 
</H1>



Some linguists believe the Yanomam languages are distantly related to the 
<A href="http://www.native-languages.org/famchi.htm">Chibchan</a> or
<A href="http://www.native-languages.org/fampan.htm">Panoan</a>
language families. 
The Yanomam languages are spoken in southern Venezuela and northwestern Brazil. 
<br><br>

